☁️ What is Cloud Computing?

Cloud computing means using the internet to store data and run applications instead of using your own computer or local server.

👉 In simple words:
You don’t save files or run software on your PC — you use online servers (cloud).

💡 Easy Example
When you use Google Drive to save files → that is cloud computing
When you watch movies on Netflix → data comes from the cloud
When you use Gmail → emails are stored in the cloud
🔑 Key Features
Storage → Save files online
Access Anywhere → Use from mobile, laptop, anywhere
No Hardware Needed → No need to buy expensive servers
Scalable → Increase or decrease resources easily
🏢 Popular Cloud Providers
Amazon Web Services (AWS)
Microsoft Azure
Google Cloud
📦 Types of Cloud Computing
IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service)
→ You get servers, storage, networking
PaaS (Platform as a Service)
→ You get a platform to build apps
SaaS (Software as a Service)
→ You use software online (like Gmail)
